  "abstract": {
    "value": "An efficient method for the synthesis of chiral tetrahydrocarbazoles (THCs) containing an allene moiety is disclosed, which was established by an enantioconvergent substitution reaction catalyzed by a chiral phosphoric acid. Racemic indolylmethanols bearing the THC motif reacted with N-methylpyrrole in the presence of the SPINOL-derived chiral phosphoric acid to give the corresponding chiral THCs with allenylsilanes in good yields with high enantioselectivities.",
    "source": "llm_from_front_matter",
